m2.1: This model includes all local and landscape predictors. 
Following the DAG, this will allow us to determine the direct effect of park size and tree cover
on butterfly occurrence. The plant species diversity predictor represents the effects
of plant size on occurrence, with some of this effect coming through either park size and/or tree cover.
Following the DAG, all other predictor estimates will reflect the total (direct) causal effect
on butterfly occurrence.

m2.2: This model removes plant diversity. This will allow us to determine the total
causal effects of park size and tree cover on occurrence. If the effect size does not
change much, then we can presume that most of the effects of park size and tree cover
are direct rather than acting through increasing plant diversity.
